FAST-RISING afrobeats singer, Kolawole Jethro aka ‘Aso’ thatmusicboy, has said that working hard in the Nigerian entertainment industry will leave a huge legacy in the industry even as a youngster. The musician, who is also a stand-up comedian, made this known in a recent chat with The Nation. Aso, an artist with more than 20 songs, made this known recently while sharing some of his plans towards the Nigerian music industry.   Netflix eyes King Of Boys’ editor Steve Sodiya     Cremate my body when I die – Femi Kuti     Ritual killings don’t produce billionaires –…   He noted that “with great contention, I am working hard to  leave a huge legacy in the music industry.” The Isanlu indigene, an afro orchestra conductor, said Lagos posed the mileage capable of helping emerging artists not to wink. - Advertisement - Aso’s prominent hit track entitled ‘Colour’ narrated the true challenges and success of every hero on earth.